is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Disabled"},{"type":"text","text":", limiting the FPS to a high value that can be consistently reached on the system can reduce input lag compared to an uncapped framerate. Since this works by ensuring the GPU load is lower than 100%, this latency reduction is only effective in GPU-bottlenecked scenarios, not CPU-bottlenecked scenarios."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"See also ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Engine\/physicsTicksPerSecond"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProjectSettings\/application\/run\/maxFps"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/engine\/maxfps"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"title":"maxFps","symbolKind":"property","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot6EngineC6maxFpss5Int32VvpZ","roleHeading":"Type Property","fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"maxFps"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int32","preciseIdentifier":"s:s5Int32V","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}]},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The maximum number of frames per second that can be rendered. A value of ","type":"text"},{"code":"0","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" means “no limit”. The actual number of frames per second may still be below this value if the CPU or GPU cannot keep up with the project logic and rendering.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Engine\/maxFps","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Engine/maxFps":{"title":"maxFps","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The maximum number of frames per second that can be rendered. A value of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0"},{"type":"text","text":" means “no limit”. The actual number of frames per second may still be below this value if the CPU or GPU cannot keep up with the project logic and rendering."}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"maxFps"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s5Int32V","text":"Int32"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/engine\/maxfps","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Engine\/maxFps"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Node/_physicsProcess(delta:)":{"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/node\/_physicsprocess(delta:)","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node\/_physicsProcess(delta:)","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Called during the physics processing step of the main loop. Physics processing means that the frame rate is synced to the physics, i.e. the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"delta"},{"type":"text","text":" variable should be constant. "},{"code":"delta","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is in seconds."}],"title":"_physicsProcess(delta:)","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"_physicsProcess"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"delta"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Double"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Engine":{"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Provides access to engine properties."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Engine"}],"title":"Engine","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/engine","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/docum